The '''Julius Shulman Institute''' (JSI) at [[Woodbury University]] promotes photography of the [[built environment]]. The JSI hosts exhibitions, workshops and symposia.<ref>{{cite web|title=About|url=http://jsi.architecture.woodbury.edu/about|website=Julius Shulman Institute|accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref>
==History== In 2005, architectural photographer [[Julius Shulman]] founded the Institute at Woodbury University. He chose a university as a home for the JSI because of his interest in education.<ref>{{cite web|title=About|url=http://jsi.architecture.woodbury.edu/about|website=Julius Shulman Institute|accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref> The endowment supports students, career artists, and commercial photographers who document the physical environment.
[[Barbara Bestor]] is Executive Director of the JSI.<ref>{{cite web|title=Contact|url=http://jsi.architecture.woodbury.edu/contact|website=Julius Shulman Institute|accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref>
==Awards== ===Excellence in Photography=== The Excellence in Photography Award is awarded annually by the Institute to honor photographers that challenge the way we look at physical space.<ref>{{cite web|title=Awards|url=http://jsi.architecture.woodbury.edu/awards|website=Julius Shulman Institute|accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref>
